20.why lazy evaluation
> “Spark uses lazy evaluation to optimize performance. Instead of executing each transformation immediately, it builds a full execution plan (DAG) and delays execution until an action is called.
> This allows Spark to apply optimizations like predicate pushdown, column pruning, and combining multiple transformations into a single stage, which reduces data movement and improves efficiency.
> It also avoids unnecessary computations — for example, if part of the data isn’t needed for the final result, Spark won’t process it at all.
> Overall, lazy evaluation helps minimize resource usage and makes distributed processing much faster and more efficient.”

